40|$|The paper {{argues for}} the {{necessity}} of a mixed approach to usability evaluation at the <b>ship’s</b> <b>bridge</b> and proposes a generic, but practical framework for this purpose. The proposed approach concerns the usability evaluation of <b>ship</b> <b>bridge</b> interactive systems and combines the biometric tools of gaze tracking & speech recording for measuring emotional user responses with usability testing. The ultimate goal of this research is to find and test the critical factors that influence the usability of <b>ship</b> <b>bridge</b> equipment and the ability to conduct fulltime system control by the marine crew. Keywords Ship’s bridge; usability; eye-tracking; evaluation, lexical analysis. 1...|$|R
